#: software.php:39
msgid "What is Linux?"
msgstr "&iquest;Qu&eacute; es Linux?"

#: foss.php:4 index.php:16 linux.php:2 linux.php:23
msgid "What is FOSS?"
msgstr "&iquest;Qu&eacute; es SLCA?"

#: foss.php:6
msgid "FOSS stands for 'Free and Open Source Software'. It is a movement started in 1983 by Richard Stallman and the <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.gnu.org/philosophy/philosophy.html\">Free Software Foundation</a> (FSF). 'Free' in this context refers to 'freedom' (as in free speech), not price (although FOSS also tends to be). As the FSF says <em>\"Free software is a matter of liberty not price\"</em> and this is an important distinction to make. Many pieces of software out there claim to be 'free', and I'm sure you have heard of terms like 'freeware' and 'shareware'. These types of software tend to be free (as in price) but not free (as in freedom)."
msgstr "SLCA significa 'Software libre y de c&oacute;digo abierto'. Es un movimiento iniciado en 1983 por Richard Stallman y la <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.gnu.org/philosophy/philosophy.es.html\">Free Software Foundation</a> (FSF). La palabra 'Free' o 'Libre' en este contexto se refiere a 'libertad' (como en libertad de expresi&oacute;n), no al precio (aunque el SLCA tiende a ello). Como dice la FSF <em>\"El software libre es un asunto de libertad no de precio\"</em> y esta es una importante distinci&oacute;n que hay que hacer. Algunos programas que existen aseguran ser 'libres', seguramente has escuchado t&eacute;rminos como 'freeware' y 'shareware'. Este tipo de software tiende a ser libre (en cuanto a precio) pero no libre (en cuanto a libertad)."

#: foss.php:8
msgid "All the software that you run on your computer has been created to work on your operating system. If you use Microsoft Windows, then the software has been 'packaged' to run on Windows. If you use Apple's OSX or even Linux then the same rule applies. Software that is 'packaged' and installed onto your computer generally exists in what is called 'binary' form or, as an 'executable'."
msgstr "Todo el software que ejecutas en tu computadora ha sido creado para funcionar con tu sistema operativo. Si usas Microsoft Windows, entonces el software ha sido 'empaquetado' para funcionar en Windows. Si utilizas OSX de Apple o incluso Linux la misma regla aplica. El software que es 'empaquetado' e instalado en tu computadora generalmente existe en una forma llamada 'binaria' o, como un 'ejecutable'."

#: foss.php:10
msgid "Binary software is 'locked' in a sense because it is in computer language. This means that it is virtually impossible for humans to see how it operates and what it is actually doing! A good example of this is spyware and virus software. When these applications are installed onto a machine it is very hard to work out exactly what they are doing. They could be sending your banking information across the internet, or grabbing all of your important passwords. You just don't know, because they are locked."
msgstr "El software binario est&aacute; de alguna manera 'bloqueado' porque est&aacute; en lenguaje de computadoras. Esto significa que es virtualmente imposible para los humanos ver c&oacute;mo funciona y qu&eacute; exactamente est&aacute; haciendo. Podr&iacute;an estar enviando tu informaci&oacute;n bancaria a trav&eacute;s de internet, o capturando todas tus claves importantes. Simplemente no lo sabes, porque est&aacute;n bloqueados."

#: foss.php:12
msgid "All computer programs are first written by humans in readable language, which is called 'source code'. Microsoft owns the source code to Windows and their products, as does Apple to theirs, etc. Think about a computer virus. If we had the source code to the virus, we would know <em>exactly</em> what it does, and could easily stop it. The virus creators, Microsoft, Apple and others do not release their code to the public, which means no-one can tell what their software is actually doing."
msgstr "Todos los programas de computadora son primero escritos por humanos en lenguaje legible, que es llamado 'c&oacute;digo fuente'. Microsoft es propietario del c&oacute;digo fuente de Windows y sus productos, as&iacute; como Apple de los suyos, etc. Piensa en un virus de computadora. Si tuvi&eacute;semos el c&oacute;digo fuente del virus, sabr&iacute;amos <em>exactamente</em> qu&eacute; hace, y podr&iacute;amos f&aacute;cilmente detenerlo. Los creadores de virus, Microsoft, Apple y otros no presentan su c&oacute;digo al p&uacute;blico, lo que significa que nadie puede saber qu&eacute; est&aacute; haciendo realmente su software."

#: foss.php:14
msgid "There are software creators around the world however, who believe that everyone has the right to know exactly what the software on their computer is doing. Not only do they release 'packaged' versions of the software but more importantly, these people make the source code to their software freely available for everyone. This is called 'open source'. One great example of open source software is <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://mozilla.com/firefox\">Mozilla Firefox</a> a free web browser for Linux, Windows and OSX, which is safe and secure. For more examples of open source software, read on (or click <a href=\"software.php\">here</a> to visit now)."
msgstr "Sin embargo existen creadores de software alrededor del mundo, que creen que todos tienen el derecho a saber exactamente qu&eacute; est&aacute; haciendo el software en su computadora. Ellos no solamente lanzan versiones 'empaquetadas' del software sino que m&aacute;s importante, hacen que el c&oacute;digo fuente de su software est&eacute; disponible libremente para todos. Esto se denomina 'c&oacute;digo abierto'. Un gran ejemplo de software de c&oacute;digo abierto es <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.mozilla-europe.org/es/\">Mozilla Firefox</a> un navegador web libre y seguro para Linux, Windows y OSX. Para m&aacute;s ejemplos de software de c&oacute;digo abierto, contin&uacute;a leyendo (o haz click <a href=\"software.php\">aqu&iacute;</a>)."

#: foss.php:16
msgid "In essence you can <em>only</em> trust open source software, because it is freely available for everyone to read in human form and see exactly what the software does. For this reason governments, other agencies, schools and individuals all around the world are switching to the security of open source software (and so should you!)."
msgstr "En resumen puedes <em>&uacute;nicamemte</em> confiar en el software de c&oacute;digo abierto, porque est&aacute; libremente disponible para que cualquiera lo revise y vea exactamente qu&eacute; es lo que hace. Por esta raz&oacute;n gobiernos, otras agencias, escuelas e individuos alrededor del mundo se est&aacute;n cambiando a la seguridad del software de c&oacute;digo abierto (&iexcl;y t&uacute; tambi&eacute;n deber&iacute;as!)."

#: gallery.php:6
msgid "To help you decide what Linux distribution you might want to try (and so you can see what Linux looks like) we have a gallery containing screenshots of recommended Linux distributions (listed <a href=\"getstarted.php#trylinux\">here</a>) for you to view. We also have screenshots of free open source software (listed <a href=\"software.php\">here</a>) so you can see what they look like if you want to give them a try."
msgstr "Para ayudarte a decidir qu&eacute; distribuci&oacute;n de Linux podr&iacute;as probar (y para que veas c&oacute;mo se ve Linux) tenemos una galer&iacute;a que contiene capturas de pantalla de distribuciones de Linux recomendadas (listadas <a href=\"getstarted.php#trylinux\">aqu&iacute;</a>) para que las revises. Tambi&eacute;n tenemos capturas de pantalla de software libre y de c&oacute;digo abierto (listadas <a href=\"software.php\">aqu&iacute;</a>) para que veas c&oacute;mo es su aspecto si deseas probarlos."

